1st Things 1st - Serious subject, Joyful Day!

We meet EVERY day, 365 days/year at 7:00am U.S. Central Time (5am Pacific / 8am Eastern).  

This is a closed meeting of Alcoholics Anonymous, meaning that it is for those who have a desire to stop drinking.

On Tuesdays, we have a topic, on Wednesday, we choose a step, and on Sundays, we have speakers. We are certainly not a glum lot! We average about 100 attendees every day and have a great group of people, predominantly from the US but across the globe as well. We begin our meeting with the long version of the serenity prayer, January 6th thought for the day, How it Works, the AA Preamble, offer big books to those who cannot afford them, and have a healthy mix of sobriety from 24 hours to 40 years. Most importantly, we like to have fun, because we are all alive!

notes:
AAOnline is a Group of recovering alcoholics that holds one hour AA meetings 4 times a day, following an Online format. Our hope is that any suffering alcoholic who reaches out for help will find it from the members in our room.
